With help from some locals, Holloway's mother and the others determined the youth had been in the casino playing in a poker tournament, according to Bearman.
"We have to wait for the investigation to finish," she said.
A fourth suspect, the disc jockey from a party boat, is also in custody.
In an interview Friday with The Associated Press, Bearman said Aruban authorities couldn't be faulted completely for failing to identify van der Sloot and the others more quickly, something she said the amateur sleuths did in less than three hours in Aruba.
